{
  "stem": "6526.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we used to-- the Judenrat use to bring soap.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We used to go into the street with the soap for the people, take them once a week or once in two weeks, because as was possible, to the bath, to the mikvah.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That's the only ritual bath-- only bath that could be.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was no lake that they could bathe and they then, of course, they didn't want to go, because they were cold to go out of the house.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In the house, they were sticking to each other and get warm.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But we had to be the bad ones to take them there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "This was the repercussion, let's say like, we are bad to them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But what we meant was good for all.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Otherwise they would-- the Germans would come, throw out, and put the house on fire, because the town had a lot of typhus.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I myself was sick of typhus and so was my brother, but we survived.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father went until they killed him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was Yom Kippur, 1942.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Warsaw was already being deported on and off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The next town-- the county town-- Minsk Mazowiecki, was deported a week before.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were expected.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Germans came and they said, we need-- and the day before, or was it on Yom Kippur '42 or the day before?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They need people to go to the camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were labor camps in the area.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The labor camps consisted of digging ditches, draining, because there was a lot of water.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they were making roads, they should not-- and they need all people should come, Yom Kippur, to go to work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A lot of them went away before, and all of them run away.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
